  "response": "\"Savdhan India,\" \"Crime Patrol,\" and similar shows are primarily dramatizations based on real-life events, but they may not always represent the actual facts of specific cases accurately. These programs often draw inspiration from true crime stories, focusing on themes of crime prevention and justice, and they may include fictional elements for entertainment purposes.\n\nWhile the crimes depicted might be based on true incidents, they are usually exaggerated or altered for dramatic effect. Additionally, the way events unfold, the characters involved, and the outcomes may differ from the real-life situations to make the stories more engaging for the audience.\n\nIf you're interested in the real-life cases that inspired these shows, it can be helpful to look up news articles or official reports to get accurate information about those events.",
